{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "g1",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -160,
      "y": 20,
      "width": 2160,
      "height": 780,
      "label": "C4 L1 · System Context — who uses Specorator, and what it talks to"
    },
    {
      "id": "g2",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -160,
      "y": 880,
      "width": 2720,
      "height": 1080,
      "label": "C4 L2 · Containers inside Specorator"
    },
    {
      "id": "g3",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -160,
      "y": 2280,
      "width": 2720,
      "height": 880,
      "label": "C4 L3 · Components & responsibilities — the Vault MCP bridge + the Trust layer"
    },
    {
      "id": "title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -160,
      "y": -220,
      "width": 1500,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "6",
      "text": "# Specorator — Architecture (C4 Model)\nContext → Container → Component. Stakeholder view. **🟩 Green = ships today (build upon, don't regress)** · **🟦 Cyan = new in v1** · **🟥 Red = safety-critical** · **🟧 Orange = people/actors** · **🟨 Yellow = legend/notes** · ⬜ Grey = external."
    },
    {
      "id": "legend",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2060,
      "y": 20,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 600,
      "color": "3",
      "text": "## Legend\n\n**🟩 Green** — exists today. Specorator builds upon these; v1 must **not** regress them.\n\n**🟦 Cyan** — new harness components added for v1.\n\n**🟥 Red** — safety-critical, fail-closed, non-negotiable.\n\n**⬜ Grey** — external systems outside Specorator.\n\n**🟧 Orange** — people / actors.\n\n**🟨 Yellow** — legend & notes.\n\n---\n**Principle:** *Agent = Model + Harness.* Keep the delegated loop; build the user-facing harness around it.\n\n**Don't reinvent:** Chat · Agent Board · Quick Actions · Orchestrator · Multi-provider already work — *extend* them."
    },
    {
      "id": "a_nontech",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 120,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**👩 Maya & Sam**\nNon-technical writer / knowledge worker. Never opened a terminal."
    },
    {
      "id": "a_power",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 320,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**👨‍💻 Devin**\nPower user. Has a CLI + subscription. Wants plan mode, subagents, MCP."
    },
    {
      "id": "a_priya",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 520,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**🔒 Priya**\nPrivacy-conscious. Sensitive folders the agent must never touch."
    },
    {
      "id": "sys",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 760,
      "y": 300,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 240,
      "color": "6",
      "text": "## Specorator\nObsidian plugin (desktop). A trustworthy agent harness around your vault.\n\n*Built on the Claudian codebase.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "ext_cli",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1600,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 140,
      "text": "**Provider CLIs** ⬜\nClaude Code · Codex · Opencode · Cursor. *Run the agent loop.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "ext_llm",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1600,
      "y": 250,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 120,
      "text": "**LLM provider APIs** ⬜\nAnthropic · OpenAI · others (BYOK)."
    },
    {
      "id": "ext_mcp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1600,
      "y": 400,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 120,
      "text": "**MCP servers** ⬜\nExternal tools the user connects."
    },
    {
      "id": "ext_web",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1600,
      "y": 550,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 110,
      "text": "**Web search** ⬜\nOpt-in, default off."
    },
    {
      "id": "ext_vault",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 760,
      "y": 590,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 120,
      "text": "**Obsidian Vault** ⬜\nYour Markdown notes, links, properties."
    },
    {
      "id": "ext_keychain",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 300,
      "y": 590,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 120,
      "text": "**OS Keychain** ⬜\nObsidian SecretStorage (Electron safeStorage under the hood). Keys never synced to the vault."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_chat",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Chat** 🟩\nSidebar conversation: send · stream · cancel · fork · resume · inline edit."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_board",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 300,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Agent Board** 🟩\nWork-orders, lanes, inbox → done. Tracks every handoff."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_qa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 660,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Quick Actions** 🟩\nSaved prompts as vault notes, one tap."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_orch",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1020,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Orchestrator** 🟩\nSplit a goal into parallel tasks; one combined answer."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_settings",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1380,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Settings & Provider tabs** 🟩\nPer-provider config · MCP · skills · agents."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_onboard",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1740,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Onboarding & Diagnostics** 🟦\nValidate CLI on enable · paste key · test connection · plain-language errors."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_hud",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2120,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Cost & Context HUD** 🟦\nLive token cost · warn before limits · one-tap compaction."
    },
    {
      "id": "c_registry",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 1340,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Provider Registry & Chat Runtimes** 🟩\nNormalises Claude / Codex / Opencode / Cursor (ACP / CLI) into one stream.\n*Owns the seam, not the loop.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "c_session",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 1340,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "**Session & history store** 🟩\n`.claudian/sessions` metadata · resume · fork."
    },
    {
      "id": "c_vaultmcp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 860,
      "y": 1340,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "## Vault MCP server 🟦\nLoopback HTTP MCP all four CLIs dial into. Gives every backend vault-native tools + shared memory.\n*Additive tool surface — not a safety chokepoint.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "c_lite",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1800,
      "y": 1540,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "## Lite provider (direct API) 🟦\nBYOK, no CLI/Node — the only zero-install path (also mobile). Read-mostly Q&A → escalates to a CLI provider for edits."
    },
    {
      "id": "c_rag",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1340,
      "y": 1540,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "## Retrieval (RAG) layer 🟦\nIndex · chunk · embed · hybrid retrieve. Pluggable backends (no-install default; Ollama/LanceDB opt-in). Grounded answers + citations."
    },
    {
      "id": "c_memory",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1400,
      "y": 1340,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Memory store (3-tier)** 🟦\nSession summaries · durable facts · profile. Markdown, in the vault."
    },
    {
      "id": "c_harness",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1800,
      "y": 1340,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "## Harness Library 🟦\nProvider-agnostic **Skills · Tools (MCP) · Rules**. Author once in a Quick-Actions-style UI → compiles to each provider's native format. *No config files.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "sf_approval",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 1700,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Approval gateway (HITL)** 🟥\nPrimary boundary. Expanded diff before write; fail-closed. Real gate on Claude; provider-mediated on Codex/Opencode; **advisory on Cursor** (no-op callback)."
    },
    {
      "id": "sf_undo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 360,
      "y": 1700,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Universal Undo — Shadow-Git** 🟥\nWhole-vault, turn-level checkpoints (gitdir outside the vault). One-click 'undo all' on **every** provider. *Not covered: out-of-vault writes, big binaries.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "sf_audit",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 780,
      "y": 1700,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Audit log** 🟥\nAppend-only · survives restart. Tool · args · result digest · decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "sf_ignore",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1180,
      "y": 1700,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**`.obsidian-agentignore`** 🟥\nDefault-deny sensitive folders. Enforced at Vault MCP / Claude gate; **advisory elsewhere** → also compiled to each provider's native ignore config."
    },
    {
      "id": "sf_egress",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1600,
      "y": 1700,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Egress allowlist & network ledger** 🟥\nWeb / API only against an allowlist. Visible network categories."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_note",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Note tools** 🟦\nread / create / edit (block-aware) · move/rename auto-updates links · delete → trash."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_struct",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 300,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Structure tools** 🟦\nfrontmatter · tags · wikilinks · backlinks · outgoing links."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_kw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 660,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Keyword search** 🟦\nFull-text across the vault."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_sem",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1020,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Semantic search (RAG)** 🟦\nsql.js index + Transformers.js embeddings · wikilink graph expansion (offline-capable). Part of the RAG layer."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_dv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1400,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Dataview & Bases** 🟦\nQuery the structured layer users already maintain."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_canvas",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1760,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Canvas / Excalidraw** 🟦\nGenerate visual outputs (v2+)."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_prov",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2120,
      "y": 2360,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Provenance / ingest** 🟦\nBlock-level citations from clips & PDFs (v2+)."
    },
    {
      "id": "tr_hitl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 2580,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**HITL approval** 🟥\nExplicit, logged, fail-closed. Safe defaults (require-approval for new users)."
    },
    {
      "id": "tr_undo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 360,
      "y": 2580,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Checkpoints / undo** 🟥\nSnapshot before write · revert in one click · separate from the user's own Git."
    },
    {
      "id": "tr_sec",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 780,
      "y": 2580,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Trifecta-breaking security** 🟥\nRule of Two. Untrusted content runs in an isolated subagent — no private data, no egress. LLM output treated as untrusted."
    },
    {
      "id": "tr_least",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1260,
      "y": 2580,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "**Least privilege** 🟥\nagentignore default-deny · egress allowlist · web search off."
    },
    {
      "id": "build_panel",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -60,
      "y": 2820,
      "width": 1020,
      "height": 240,
      "color": "4",
      "text": "## Build upon — don't reinvent 🟩\nSpecorator **extends** what already works; v1 must not regress it:\n- **Chat** (send / stream / cancel / fork / resume / inline edit)\n- **Agent Board** work-orders · **Quick Actions** · **Orchestrator**\n- **Multi-provider** · **Plan mode** · `/` `#` `$` · **subagents** · **MCP**\n\nNew components *attach to* these surfaces — they don't replace them."
    },
    {
      "id": "regression_note",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1000,
      "y": 2820,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 240,
      "color": "3",
      "text": "## Regression guard 🟨\nEvery new harness component must leave the existing feature matrix intact.\n\nVault MCP tools surface **inside** today's Chat & Agent Board. Undo & approval **wrap** the existing runtime seam. Memory feeds the **existing** prompt path.\n\n*Net-new value, zero feature loss.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "hl_hdr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1960,
      "y": 2820,
      "width": 580,
      "height": 60,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Harness Library — provider-agnostic, Quick-Actions-style**"
    },
    {
      "id": "hl_skills",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1960,
      "y": 2890,
      "width": 185,
      "height": 170,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Skills** 🟦\nWorkflows authored once → each provider's native skill format."
    },
    {
      "id": "hl_tools",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2160,
      "y": 2890,
      "width": 185,
      "height": 170,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Tools (MCP)** 🟦\nConnect once → all providers. A gallery, not JSON."
    },
    {
      "id": "hl_rules",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2360,
      "y": 2890,
      "width": 185,
      "height": 170,
      "color": "5",
      "text": "**Rules** 🟦\nGuidance once → applied everywhere."
    }
  ],
